aims-os-math (1.0) bookworm; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
    + Pulls the AIMS OS scientific computing stack: Python SciPy
      ecosystem (numpy, scipy, pandas, matplotlib, sympy, sklearn,
      statsmodels, networkx), JupyterLab + ipywidgets, SageMath with
      fr/en docs, Maxima/wxMaxima, GNU Octave plus the scientific
      add-on modules, R with the tidyverse and rmarkdown, full TeX
      Live with French and English language packs, TeXstudio and
      biber, GeoGebra and gnuplot, gdb / valgrind and the
      OpenBLAS / LAPACK / FFTW / HDF5 / GMP / MPFR development
      headers for numerical software.

